{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "ucf_counterfactual",
    "description": "Counterfactual confirmation sweep: for each unique user_split value that produced\na v26_dominant outcome in user_weight_threshold or lhs_user_weight_prim, re-run\nwith user_custody_fraction set to near-zero (0.001) \u2014 negligible user weight.\n\nRESEARCH QUESTION:\nAre the 34 v26 wins in the user-weight sweeps caused by user weight activation,\nor are they baseline PRIM-zone outcomes that would occur regardless of UCF?\n\nDESIGN:\n- 30 scenarios: one per unique user_split value from the 34 v26 wins\n  (5 split values appear at multiple UCF levels and are deduplicated)\n- user_custody_fraction fixed at 0.001 (negligible \u2014 effectively the\n  pre-activation calibration; user weight is ~0.001 \u00d7 65.9% of circulating\n  supply \u2248 0.07% active, well below any threshold of influence)\n- All pool/econ params fixed at PRIM midpoints \u2014 identical to user_weight sweeps\n- economic_split=0.60, pool_committed_split=0.35: same contested baseline\n\nINTERPRETATION:\nFor each scenario:\n  - Counterfactual = v27 \u2192 the original v26 win IS user-weight-caused (flip confirmed)\n  - Counterfactual = v26 \u2192 the outcome is a PRIM baseline effect; user weight\n    was not causal (the parameter combination favors v26 regardless)\n\nEXPECTED RESULT:\nScenarios at higher user_split (sp \u2265 0.50) are likely v27 at UCF=0.001 \u2014\nthose v26 wins were user-caused. Scenarios at lower split (sp < 0.35) may\nstay v26 \u2014 the PRIM midpoints may inherently favor v26 at low user_split.\nThe transition point in split where baseline flips from v27 to v26 will\ncleanly separate the two populations.\n\nCOMBINED WITH ORIGINAL DATA:\nCross-reference with user_weight_threshold and lhs_user_weight_prim to produce\na table mapping each of the 34 original v26 wins to:\n  [UCF=0 baseline] \u00d7 [UCF=actual result] \u2192 causal classification\n\nRUNTIME (1 server, 6 namespaces):\n- 30 scenarios / 6 namespaces = 5 per namespace\n- ~3.6 hours per scenario (2016-block retarget, duration=13000s)\n- ~18 hours wall-clock\n",
    "spec_file": "tools/sweep/specs/ucf_counterfactual.yaml",
